    "body": "### Problem\n\nSuggested snapshot after test fail may contain erroneous `screen:add_extra_attr_ids` call.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Add the following test to ['tests/functional/example_spec.lua'](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/test/functional/example_spec.lua):\n\n    ```lua\n    describe('test', function()\n      clear()\n\n      n.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'aaa' })\n      local ns_id = n.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\n      local opts = { end_row = 0, end_col = 3, hl_group = 'DiagnosticInfo' }\n      n.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns_id, 0, 0, opts)\n\n      local screen = Screen.new(20, 5)\n      screen:expect('')\n    end)\n    ```\n2. Run `TEST_FILE=test/functional/example_spec.lua make functionaltest`. Notice the following output:\n\n    ```\n    Snapshot:\n    screen:add_extra_attr_ids({\n      [31] = { foreground = Screen.colors.LightBlue },\n    })\n\n    screen:expect([[\n      {31:^aaa}                 |\n      {1:~                   }|*3\n                          |\n    ]])\n    ```\n\n    Adding `screen:add_extra_attr_ids` with index 31 and rerunning tests leads to a `test/functional/ui/screen.lua:270: extra attr ids should be at least 100 or be strings` error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSuggested snapshot on test fail works with copy-paste. In the repro steps it should result into index 101 and not 31.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n`master` branch (15d57ab0ba5e)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have the same functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS 6.15.8-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom source",
